The paper discusses deep convolutional neural networks and their mathematical analysis, which are typically studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of different semi-discrete frames in distinct network layers suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on invariance and deformation stability could also make it relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
